      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"8. SOUL OF FIRE boasts a strong record this journey here with four wins and four minors from 10 tries. Comes off a (19.91) win last time, scoring by 6 lengths in a Grade 5 over 350m at this track. Appeals as a leading chance in this. 2. WHERE'S THE BOSS filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Soul Of Fire (20.31) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Must be included in calculations. 1. NINITA took the sit on the lead but levelled up to score (20.23) at this track in a Grade 5 over 350m. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Can make it back-to-back wins. 5. CANE TOAD placed last time and is worth some thought.\",\"runners\":[8,2,1,5],\"exclusive\":false}",
